Date: Fri 23 May 2014
OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2014; 27(22) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=15309


Anthrax, Botswana
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 23 May 2014 from Dr Letlhogile Modisa, director, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Gaborone, Botswana

Summary
Report type: immediate notification (final report)
Date of start of the event: 28 Apr 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 22 May 2014
Date event resolved: 23 May 2014
Reason for notification: re-occurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Sep 2008
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Kazima Forest, Chobe National Park, Chobe, Chobe
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Apr 2014
Outbreak status: Resolved (23 May 2014)
Epidemiological unit: not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
African elephant (_Loxodonta africana_ (Elephantidae) / 71 227 / 1 / 0 / 0
Affected population: this is a protected national park in the northern part of the country in Chobe District. Elephants here are all wild and free ranging. The park holds around 72 000 wild elephants that roam between Botswana, Zambia, Zimbabwe, and Namibia.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
African elephant (_Loxodonta africana_ (Elephantidae) / 71227 / 1 / 1 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
African elephant (_Loxodonta africana_ (Elephantidae) / 0 / 0 / 100 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: an elephant was found dead in the Kazima forest by the Department of Wildlife and National Parks officers during routine patrols. They noted unclotted blood oozing from the mouth, whereupon they collected blood samples for submission to the Botswana National Veterinary Laboratory as they suspected anthrax. The national park often gets flares of outbreaks of anthrax in different wildlife species, but no cases have been recorded in livestock for years now in the adjacent livestock zone as they are regularly vaccinated against anthrax. The carcass was burnt to ashes.

Control measures
Measures applied: no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Botswana National Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / African Elephant inoculation test / 22 May 2014 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak on the northern border of Botswana can be seen on the on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

